</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Sexual dimorphism. The female differs from the male only by the somewhat robuster body, simple metatibiae and by the apically weakly notched anal ventrite.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">
Etymology. The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[586,721,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[586,721,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” indicates the westernmost distribution of the entire 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[1335,1436,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[161,188,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[204,276,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">
Differential diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[461,761,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[461,562,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[580,608,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[626,761,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[770,864,295,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[770,864,295,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs, except for the distribution, from the most similar and most probably also related species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[675,831,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[675,699,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[715,743,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[759,831,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very weakly uneven and somewhat longer elytra, wider pronotum, fine, inner serration of the male metatibiae (
<figureCitation box="[890,973,367,393]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) and by the somewhat different shape of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[366,457,403,429]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Figs. 18</figureCitation>
vs. 21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[199,433,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[199,300,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[317,345,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[361,433,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[489,709,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[489,513,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[530,558,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[574,709,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[717,809,439,465]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[717,809,439,465]" pageId="11" pageNumber="533" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seem to be vicariant species, the former widely distributed in southern Africa and along the eastern coast as far as 
<collectingCountry box="[848,921,475,501]" name="Kenya" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(westerly to 
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1136,475,501]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">DRC</collectingCountry>
), and the latter distributed along the westAfrican coast between 
<collectingCountry box="[570,637,511,537]" name="Benin" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Benin</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[692,784,511,537]" name="Senegal" pageId="11" pageNumber="533">Senegal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
